The paper presents an algorithmic solution to a variant of the constrained LCS problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of string algorithms. The paper also mentions the use of run-length encoding (RLE) to compress the input strings, which is a common technique in data compression and falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also presents an algorithmic improvement over a previous algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
